reviewText: Not as relevant and updated anymore.
The project doesn't have the correct version of the chrome driver. So an exception is always thrown in Eclipse IDE.
The google chrome driver in the exercises needs to be updated, it throws errors and the tests get skipped.  The content of the course is good.
Setup was missing required driver, therefore none of the written code got executed as expected
Good Course

Overall the course was good for beginners with some knowledge on the selenium knowledge. Would have been better if there was more explanation done on the TestNG priority settings of the methods and how they can be avoided to get looped execution. Good explanation on finding xPath for the  webelements.User working window had poor resolution.

The course itself (or project) is actually pretty cool and lets you understand more about automation in tests. But the platform is horrible. It's slow, hard to view the local machine and video at the same time, and also very buggy.
I WOULD LIKE TO PRACTICE MORE ON THIS TOPIC .THANKS FOR THE EXCELLENT GUIDELINES YOU PROVIDED

I do like the cloud workspace and writing the code along with the instructor however the chromedriver.exe that is on the workspace does not match the version of chrome being used so it will not execute the tests the same way as the instructor is. It will fail if there is not a newer chromedriver.exe installed to match the chrome browser version.
